      "span_text": "These findings are in good accordance with the influent C:N ratios described by Grady et al.  , namely, a BOD 5 / NH 4 -N ratio lower than 4 belongs to severe carbon deficiency, and the range between 4 and 6 represents marginal carbon availability, because it does not meet the safe criteria of efficient denitrification."
